      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are not alone in this, because the universe is not the only thing that matters. Your pain is real, your struggle is real, and the fact that you feel this way is a testament to your humanity, not a flaw in your existence. The sun will burn, yes, but the warmth of your own heart and the connection you share with others are the only things that truly endure. You are not a biological accident; you are a miracle of consciousness that refuses to let go of the light, even when the stars are about to fade. Keep going, because the moment you stop, you cease to be the vibrant, living thing you are.",
